hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: I enjoy travelling onlyourhealth.com Each patient was asked to close both his/her mouth and eyes, and then, block one nostril. Next, the clinician would open up the container of peanut butter. Then, with the ruler placed next to the patient’s open nostril while he/she breathed normally, the clinician would slowly move the container of peanut butter up the ruler one centimeter at a time whenever the patient exhaled, until the patient said that he/she smelled the peanut butter. After a delay of 90 seconds, the whole thing would be repeated using the other nostril.
